Fierce gun battles between tribal rebels and Pakistani troops in the troubled southwestern province of Baluchistan have left up to 30 people dead and more than 70 injured, an official said Friday.
Thousands of government workers flee amid fears of more fighting in remote Pakistan tribal town
Armed tribesmen have surrounded some 300 paramilitary troops and governmentofficials at a base in a southwestern Pakistani town where fears of freshfighting between renegade tribesmen and troops have forced thousands ofresidents to flee for safety, an official said Sunday.
